# The Lokum – Anatolia & Beyond

Welcome to the digital home of The Lokum, a premium culinary destination located in the heart of Bengaluru, India. This project is a high-end, immersive frontend experience designed to mirror the Fire & Tradition of authentic Anatolian and Turkish cuisine.

![The Lokum Brand](images/logo-footer.png)

## The Vision
The Lokum isn't just a restaurant; it's a sensory journey. This website was built to capture that essence—combining modern web technology with timeless heritage storytelling. From the warmth of the wood-fired ovens to the intricate geometry of Anatolian art, every pixel is curated to offer a luxury digital storefront.

## The Menu Experience
The standalone menu page is designed as a 3D Digital Gallery. 
- 3D Tilt Interaction: Powered by VanillaTilt.js, each menu page reacts to your touch or mouse, creating a physical sense of browsing a real menu.
- Curated Categories: Beyond Turkish classics, the menu features specialized sections like Kashmiri Specials, authentic Pides, and an extensive Mezze palette.
- Ambient Atmosphere: A subtle scaling animation on the background and watermark typography ensures the interface feels alive.

Key Features

 1. Cinematic Visual Storytelling
- Hero Experience: A high-definition video background that immediately immerses users in the restaurant's atmosphere.
- Story Section: A parallax-driven Our Story layout that uses staggered image stacks to tell the tale of Turkish hospitality.

### 2. Advanced Interaction System
- GSAP Magic: Powered by the GreenSock Animation Platform, the site features ultra-smooth, high-performance transitions.
- Ultra-Smooth Gallery: A 3D-perspective gallery where items react to your mouse movement and scroll position using ScrollTrigger.
- Moving Moments: A cinematic video grid showing the rhythm of the kitchen with live-pulsing indicators and hover-zoom effects.
- Luxury Contact Suite: Interactive contact cards featuring a mouse-follow glow effect for a premium, tactile feel.

 3. Smart & Responsive Architecture
- Asymmetric Navigation: A unique, floating navbar that adapts on scroll and features a custom-animated hamburger menu.
- Adaptive Theme: Supports both Dark Mode and Light Mode to suit different user preferences.
- Continental Specials: A dedicated feature-grid for global flavors including Chicken Caesar Salads, Crumb Fried Chicken, and Chicken Alfredo.
- Mobile Optimized: Every interaction—from the Instagram reels fix to the video autoplay—is engineered for seamless performance on iOS and Android.

 4. Heritage & Spaces
- Ramzan Specials: Integrated logic for seasonal promotions, including countdown timers and dedicated platter highlights.
- The Majlis: A dedicated section showcasing gathering spaces with cultural patterns and atmospheric glow effects.

5. Seamless External Integrations
- Online Dining: Integrated direct ordering via Zomato and Swiggy (coming soon) with a focus on artisan packaging.
- Priority Reservations: Native links to Dineout, EazyDiner, and Zomato Gold for curated table access.
- Trust Indicators: Real-time look at customer sentiment with an integrated Google Reviews 4.5+ star badge.

 Technical Stack
- HTML5: Pure semantic structure for SEO and accessibility.
- CSS3: Extensive use of CSS variables, complex gradients, 3D transforms, and backdrop-filter for that glassmorphism look.
- JavaScript: Custom modular architecture wrapped in a safe IIFE.
- Libraries: GSAP, ScrollTrigger, AOS, VanillaTilt, Instagram Embed API.

## Design Philosophy
Unlike most modern quick websites, The Lokum focuses on a premium, cinematic pace. 
- High-Art Typography: Pairing Playfair Display with Inter to create a balance of tradition and modernity.
- Selective Motion: Animations are intentional, designed to guide the eye rather than distract from the photography.
- No Placeholders: Every image and video in this repository is a high-fidelity asset shot specifically for the brand.

## Project Structure
index.html: The grand landing page
style.css: The master design system
script.js: The interactive engine
menu/menu.html: Dedicated menu experience
images/: Brand assets and photography
videos/: Cinematic hero clips
food/: Specialized food photography
Culinary Journey/: Heritage-specific visual assets

## Local Setup
To experience The Lokum in its full glory:
1. Clone the Repository: Download the project files to your local machine.
2. Use a Local Server: Because the site uses external libraries and video assets, it is highly recommended to run it through a local server.
3. Browser Support: Optimized for modern versions of Chrome, Safari, and Edge.

